caption.body: Scenic wallpaper from China for export starting in the late 17th century certainly served as an inspiration for the French scenic wallpaper that followed in the nineteenth century. Zuber et Cie’s Décor Chinois mimics Chinese wallpaper with its shallow perspective, foregoing the background and foreground typically depicted in French panoramic papers. “Zuber: The Art of French Scenic Wallpaper” is on display, pre-security in the International Terminal. http://bit.ly/ZuberScenicWallpaper
